+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HQR1hkKtzZgJhAVw8Di1mc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me make the design decisions and write the plan.\n\n**Design Decisions (Autopilot):**\n\n**Q1: Module Architecture?**\n→ Choosing: **(B) Multiple focused modules** — cell-ref parser, formula parser, dependency graph, evaluator, and Spreadsheet facade. Reasoning: Keeps each concern testable and manageable without over-engineering.\n\n**Q2: Formula Parsing Approach?**\n→ Choosing: **Recursive descent parser with a tokenizer**. Reasoning: Simple to implement, handles operator precedence naturally, no external dependencies needed.\n\n**Q3: Dependency Graph Strategy?**\n→ Choosing: **Adjacency list with topological sort for recalculation**. Reasoning: Simple Map-based adjacency list; on cell change, find all transitive dependents via BFS/DFS, then topologically sort for correct evaluation order. Circular detection via cycle check during sort.\n\n**Q4: Reactive Update Strategy?**\n→ Choosing: **Eager recalculation on set()**. Reasoning: Simpler than lazy/dirty-flag approach. When a cell changes, immediately recompute all dependents in topological order. Given the library nature (no UI frame batching needed), eager is cleaner.\n\n**Q5: AST Representation?**\n→ Choosing: **Discriminated union types for AST nodes** (NumberLiteral, StringLiteral, BoolLiteral, CellRef, RangeRef, BinaryOp, FunctionCall). Reasoning: TypeScript discriminated unions give exhaustive switch checks."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":392,"cache_read_input_tokens":23339,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":392},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2b435673-0abc-4c8d-ad2c-d0d1b51f9f19","uuid":"fae57748-0449-4a88-b8ae-5b0a00d1e55b"}
